"We need to be careful about how we identify the true emergence of puberty," said Dr. Lawrence Silverman, a pediatrician working at the Goryeb Children's Hospital in Morristown, New Jersey.
Parents should not hesitate to ask their pediatrician for advice on how to talk to their child.
"This may mean having a conversation sooner than expected," Kaplowitz explained.
